# .cursorrules

## Project: SMB Bookkeeper
A WhatsApp-based AI bookkeeping assistant for Nigeria's informal economy.

## Architecture
- Backend: Python 3.12+ / FastAPI / Supabase / Twilio / Google Gemini / Paystack
- Frontend: React 19 / React Router 7 / shadcn/ui / Tailwind v4 / Recharts / Framer Motion
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with real-time subscriptions
- Payments: Paystack (Nigerian payment gateway)
- Messaging: Twilio WhatsApp Sandbox (development) -> Meta Cloud API (production)
- LLM: Google Gemini 2.0 Flash (free tier)

## Code Style
- Backend: Python with type hints, async/await, Pydantic models for validation
- Frontend: TypeScript strict mode, functional components, hooks only
- Use shadcn/ui components wherever possible (Card, Table, Badge, Button, Tabs, etc.)
- Tailwind CSS for all styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Use CSS variables for colors (defined in globals.css)
- All monetary values displayed with ₦ symbol and thousand separators
- All data numbers use JetBrains Mono font (font-mono class)
- Dark mode by default (bg-primary / #0A0A0B)

## Key Libraries
- @tanstack/react-query for all data fetching and caching
- framer-motion for animations (page transitions, list animations, number count-ups)
- recharts for all charts (AreaChart, BarChart, LineChart)
- date-fns for date formatting and manipulation
- numeral for number formatting
- lucide-react for icons

## Conventions
- File naming: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities
- Route components live in src/routes/
- Reusable components in src/components/
- shadcn components in src/components/ui/
- Supabase client and types in src/lib/
- All API calls go through @tanstack/react-query or src/lib/api.ts
- Backend routes are in app/routes/, services in app/services/, DB in app/db/

## Nigerian Context
- Currency: Nigerian Naira (₦ / NGN) — always display with ₦ symbol
- Amounts in kobo for Paystack (multiply by 100)
- Common trade items: rice, cement, garri, sugar, oil, milk, noodles, paint, roofing sheets
- Customer names: Nigerian names (Alhaji Musa, Mama Joy, Chief Okafor, etc.)
- Language: English + Pidgin English in WhatsApp messages
- "15k" = 15,000 / "2.5m" = 2,500,000

## Do NOT
- Do not use Next.js — this project uses React Router 7
- Do not install unnecessary packages
- Do not use Inter, Roboto, or Arial fonts
- Do not use purple gradients or generic AI aesthetics
- Do not use class components
- Do not write comments that just restate the code
